contents.title: A Housing Crisis for Seniors
contents.description_html: But suburban homes were originally designed, and for the most part still are, for young families - and for drivers. They are typically surrounded by other single-family houses. Lacking a fitter partner or a network of helpful neighbors and caring family members, older residents can end up feeling isolated, unable to do basic errands or keep up their property.
